14:15.000 --> 14:16.100
It's my treat.

14:16.100 --> 14:17.767
No, no, no,
I'm a grown man.

14:17.767 --> 14:20.033
I can't have my mom buying me
shirts, slacks,

14:20.033 --> 14:22.300
boxer briefs
and possibly dress shoes.

14:23.133 --> 14:24.400
You're my son, Alan.

14:24.400 --> 14:27.066
I want nothing more
than to see you happy.

14:27.066 --> 14:30.066
And not dressed like
an unemployed lesbian.

14:32.266 --> 14:36.800
Now, give me your thumb.

14:36.800 --> 14:38.767
You've never been arrested,
have you?

14:41.800 --> 14:44.066
#Men.#

14:44.066 --> 14:46.100
Berta, these
fish sticks are great.

14:46.100 --> 14:47.467
Thank you.

14:47.467 --> 14:50.633
My secret is I take 'em
out of the freezer.

14:50.633 --> 14:52.934
Well, kudos.

14:57.633 --> 14:59.000
Hey, where's my dad?

14:59.000 --> 15:00.900
(sighs)

15:00.900 --> 15:02.166
Damn it.

15:02.166 --> 15:04.333
Pay up.

15:06.867 --> 15:09.433
Thought for sure he'd stay
oblivious until Monday.

15:10.333 --> 15:12.900
Well, "obliviously,"
you were wrong.

15:15.367 --> 15:16.900
Charlie, can I talk to you
for a minute?

15:16.900 --> 15:17.967
What's up?

15:17.967 --> 15:19.667
Let's talk upstairs.

15:19.667 --> 15:21.467
Sure.

15:25.567 --> 15:27.734
Here's your cut.

15:32.000 --> 15:34.166
No, you didn't do
anything wrong.

15:34.166 --> 15:35.867
Oh, cool.

15:35.867 --> 15:37.500
So what's up?

15:37.500 --> 15:39.000
You want a quickie?

15:39.000 --> 15:40.967
No.

15:40.967 --> 15:43.200
I just got a call
from the plastic surgeon

15:43.200 --> 15:44.467
and they had a cancellation,

15:44.467 --> 15:46.734
so they can squeeze me
in tomorrow morning.

15:46.734 --> 15:48.734
Tomorrow?

15:48.734 --> 15:50.834
But... that's so soon.

15:50.834 --> 15:52.200
Why put it off?

15:52.200 --> 15:54.800
Well, I was hoping
we'd have time

15:54.800 --> 15:56.867
to go away for a few days.

15:56.867 --> 15:58.800
You know, one last fling,

15:58.800 --> 16:01.233
just the four of us.

16:02.333 --> 16:03.800
You've flung them plenty,
Charlie.

16:03.800 --> 16:06.433
Oh, come on, just
give me some more time.

16:06.433 --> 16:09.166
Time for what?
Time to talk
you out of this.

16:09.166 --> 16:10.734
You said you were
going to support me.

16:10.734 --> 16:12.667
Yeah, but when do I get
my support?

16:12.667 --> 16:13.633
What are you talking about?

16:13.633 --> 16:15.834
This decision
affects both of us.

16:15.834 --> 16:17.066
I should get a vote.

16:17.066 --> 16:18.667
You're not the one in pain.

16:18.667 --> 16:21.633
(cries):
Then why does it hurt so much?

16:25.467 --> 16:27.734
Oh, you're just
making it worse!

16:29.100 --> 16:31.300
#Men.#

16:31.300 --> 16:33.567
I love my new
silk jammies, Mom.

16:34.367 --> 16:36.266
It's like wearing
a baby seal.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.700
Well, I'm glad you
like them, dear.

16:42.700 --> 16:45.834
Oh, and I thought,
tomorrow,

16:45.834 --> 16:48.100
I could take you
to my hair stylist.

16:48.100 --> 16:50.633
Get you one of those hip,
new spiky looks.

16:50.633 --> 16:51.934
Oh, that sounds like fun.

16:51.934 --> 16:53.433
Although I'm only
two haircuts away

16:53.433 --> 16:56.100
from a free one
at the barber college.

16:56.100 --> 16:57.533
Oh, nonsense.

16:57.533 --> 16:59.800
You deserve to be
pampered a little bit.

16:59.800 --> 17:01.066
I kind of do, don't I?

17:01.066 --> 17:02.734
Yes, you do.

17:02.734 --> 17:05.900
I just have to be careful
not to make you too attractive.

17:05.900 --> 17:09.599
(chuckles)
I don't want to lose
my fella to another gal.

17:09.599 --> 17:11.567
(chortles)

17:11.567 --> 17:13.900
Your fella. Funny.

17:13.900 --> 17:15.900
Well, I'm serious.

17:15.900 --> 17:18.900
You'll always be my fella.

17:18.900 --> 17:23.032
And I'll always be
your best gal, right?

17:26.599 --> 17:28.800
Okay.

17:29.734 --> 17:33.734
And I've been thinking,
this is a big house.

17:33.734 --> 17:37.667
And you and I are clearly
not the marrying kind,

17:37.667 --> 17:42.266
so... why don't you
just move in?

17:43.100 --> 17:44.500
Here?

17:44.500 --> 17:47.233
Sure. Why not?

17:47.233 --> 17:50.066
Can't you see how you and me

17:50.066 --> 17:51.967
are meant to be?

17:53.633 --> 17:57.133
Well, we're meant to be
mother and son.

17:57.133 --> 17:59.800
That's a given.

17:59.800 --> 18:02.000
It's how we're livin'.

18:02.867 --> 18:06.100
Very clever.

18:08.200 --> 18:11.166
Of course,
there is a certain

18:11.166 --> 18:13.433
financial imbalance.

18:13.433 --> 18:15.533
But I'm sure that we can

18:15.533 --> 18:18.333
come up with a plan that
meets both of our needs.

18:18.333 --> 18:19.700
Plan? There's a,
there's a plan?

18:19.700 --> 18:22.867
Of course there's a plan.

18:24.400 --> 18:27.467
I mean, I'm a vibrant
woman now, Alan,

18:27.467 --> 18:30.266
but there will come
a time when I won't be able

18:30.266 --> 18:33.934
to fend for myself and I don't
want to pay some stranger

18:33.934 --> 18:37.834
to dress me and feed me
and carry me to the bath,

18:37.834 --> 18:39.700
soap up a wash cloth

18:39.700 --> 18:42.834
and give me a good,
thorough cleaning.

18:42.834 --> 18:45.367
Thanks, Mom! I'll call you.

18:48.100 --> 18:50.400
That should keep him away
for a while.

18:50.400 --> 18:53.400
#Men.#

18:53.400 --> 18:55.000
(crying)

18:56.467 --> 18:58.100
Are you sure you're
gonna be okay?

18:58.100 --> 18:59.967
I'm fine.

19:01.800 --> 19:03.333
Would you do me
a little favor?

19:03.333 --> 19:05.066
What?

19:05.066 --> 19:06.934
Go like this.

19:09.433 --> 19:11.066
For old time's sake.

19:11.900 --> 19:13.033
NURSE:
Chelsea?

19:13.033 --> 19:15.433
Ready for you.
Oh, God, this is it.

19:16.633 --> 19:18.166
Take a deep breath,
Charlie.

19:18.166 --> 19:20.667
I will if you will.

19:20.667 --> 19:23.467
It's still gonna be me,
just a little smaller.

19:23.467 --> 19:25.100
I know.

19:25.100 --> 19:26.600
I guess the good news is

19:26.600 --> 19:28.433
